reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice clean looking and holds a lot, spout feature is cool
reviews.reviewText: My mountain cabin has a rustic kitchen and no dishwasher. My typical plastic dish rack was gross and didn’t hold much. On Thanksgiving I put this one to the test. It did well. Granted it didn’t hold the platters and pans etc but I can see for a small crowd it will do nicely. It looks clean which I like as well as the drainer spout feature. I did find it a little difficult to attach the top rack until I took a photo and zoomed it up. Hook goes under the bottom of rack over in the middle through to the top rack with all hooks pointing out. For attaching the top rack, hold your breath, hold one side then kind of force it into place on top. Once in it’s very secure. I think it will work well for me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy construction plenty of space!
reviews.reviewText: To assemble the top tier, I did watch the video someone posted, since the directions were not clear, it was very easy. I have 10 inch square plates, so when I placed them diagonally they fit perfectly, with plenty of room. I love the silverware holder it is double the length of my old one. The cup holder is sturdy, it has a tray underneath and a drying mat, all for a good price. I'm happy with this purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good value for money
reviews.reviewText: Been using this a couple months now. It gets lots of use, easy to store lots of dishes in it, don't use the dishwasher as often as we used to. Good design, even has a place to put a cutting board where it drips into the sink. The biggest problem is that the legs are only a couple of millimeters long, so if you have even a low lip around your sink, you'll have to block the rack up in order for it to drain to the sink. We have it perched on a couple of wooden blocks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The instructions stink, but the product is great
reviews.reviewText: My sister and I finally figured out that you have to force the end of the sides into the smaller top shelf to get it to work. Then it is sturdy and wonderful. It fit under our cabinets to boot. We highly recommend this product!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love it!
reviews.reviewText: I like everything about this dish rack. It's genius for draining water! Love the color, the size. It's well made and as described. I'd buy it again. But it might be awhile as this one looks durable and will last a long time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great dish rack
reviews.reviewText: So I took my chance on this dish rack. I was looking for a large dish rack that was black. After reading tons of reviews on several different racks I ended up chosing this rack. I really like the style, the knife compartment part, & the way it strains the water. So far it's been great. Enough for my dishes and ended up being the perfect size. Of course, after having it for several months, the water marks are there, but that happens to all racks. I would definitely recommend this rack. I will purchase again, when I need to replace.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Missing Part, Slightly Inaccurate
reviews.reviewText: Recieved the product very fast after purchasing. Arrived in excellent condition. It took a little time & patience to assemble. Instructions weren't the worst I've seen, but not exactly straight forward with every step. Works great so far & feels sturdy, even with having 2 levels. Overall a little more compact than I was expecting (and much more than the last drying rack I had) but gers the job done, just won't be able to hold as many items.I deducted 2 stars because - 1. The water drain spout is not NEARLY as long as they make it look in the photos. I purchased the two tier drying rack and no matter what direction I rotate the spout, it barely reaches the end of each edge. This means you have to put the edge of the rack right up against the edge of your sink, unless you'd like to have to wipe down your counter every single time. I strongly dislike this short spout and didn't appreciate that inaccurate advertisement.2. My dish rack did not come with the cup holder. Definitely disappointed with that.All-in-all, it's just okay. It'll do the job for now, but for the price, I expect better. Not something I would repurchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great dish drying rack.
reviews.reviewText: I love this drying rack. It fits everything. I really LOVEthe cutting board attachment. I use it for small sheet pans as well as cutting boards. The Compartment for silverware is great. It has 3 compartments in it. So I can do my spoons and won forks in another knives and other things in the third one. And keep things separated easier to dry and put away. The top tier is easy to put on and can be removed if not needed everyday.

Great dish rack. The size is just perfect for my apartment counter and still able to hold all my large dishes and cookware. Sturdy metal frame with a plastic base, and the moveable spout is convenient. Like the addition of the cup holders and drying towel!
Once assembled, it is very sturdy and holds a surprising amount of dishes. Makes my kitchen counter look SO much tidier.
Good solid product. Doesn’t quite fit on the sink drainer but a nice product.
Good size, I wish the drain spout extended a bit longer.
